cluster_classes.class_description: Normative concepts used to evaluate the ethical acceptability of AI systems and their impacts, including bias as a harm mechanism and fairness/equity as desired conditions.
cluster_classes.evidence_excerpt: AI bias as an ethical concern and damage mechanism; ensuring fairness and equity in decision-making processes.

members.entity_description: Systematic, unfair, or discriminatory tendencies in AI systems arising from biased or incomplete data, design choices, or deployment contexts, which can disadvantage certain groups or lead to inequitable outcomes.
The quality of decisions or processes being impartial and just across affected groups.
Condition where outcomes and opportunities are adjusted to account for structural disadvantages.

cluster_classes.class_description: Conceptual and textual treatments of ethical dilemmas arising in the development and deployment of artificial intelligence systems, including both the abstract moral issues and documents explicitly discussing them.
cluster_classes.evidence_excerpt: Both refer to ethical dilemmas specific to AI development; one as a recurring ethical concept, the other as a document title on the same topic.

members.entity_description: Complex moral conflicts and issues that arise in the design, development, and deployment of artificial intelligence technologies, including concerns such as privacy, bias, accountability, transparency, and societal impact.
Textual discussion focused on ethical dilemmas arising from the development of artificial intelligence systems.

remarks: This class is now empty after splitting its members; consider removing or fully deprecating it in the next cleanup phase.

cluster_classes.class_description: Normative concepts that govern how AI should be developed and deployed, including explicit rules, high-level moral principles, and calls to act in a responsible and ethical manner.
cluster_classes.evidence_excerpt: Normative guidance for responsible, ethical AI development and deployment, including rules and principles.

members.entity_description: Explicit normative rules and principles intended to govern the responsible development and deployment of AI technologies.
Moral guidelines intended to shape how AI technologies are developed and used.
A mode of developing and deploying AI that adheres to ethical principles and responsibility.

splits.name: AI Ethics Dilemmas (Concept)
splits.description: The general ethical dilemma concept in AI development, covering recurring moral conflicts around privacy, bias, accountability, transparency, and societal impact.

splits.name: AI Ethics Dilemma Documents
splits.description: Documents and texts that explicitly discuss ethical dilemmas in the development and deployment of AI systems.

args.justification: ClsC_891fa7d2 mixes a conceptual ethical dilemma entity with a concrete document entity, indicating an overloaded class that should be split into a concept class and a document-focused class.
args.remark: After the split, the source class will have no remaining members and can be reviewed for deprecation or merging in a later step.

args.new_description: Normative and evaluative concepts (e.g., bias, fairness, equity) used to assess the ethical acceptability of AI systems and their impacts.
args.justification: ClsC_42a3ff76 cleanly represents core evaluative concepts in AI ethics; aligning its type_hint and adding a shared Class_Group connects it with related AI ethics governance classes.

args.new_description: Normative rules, guidelines, and high-level principles that govern how AI should be developed and deployed in a responsible and ethical manner.
args.justification: ClsC_da406864 groups explicit ethical guidelines and principles for AI; refining its type_hint and assigning the same Class_Group clarifies its role within AI ethics governance.

args.new_description: The conceptual category of ethical dilemmas arising in AI design, development, and deployment, including conflicts over privacy, bias, accountability, transparency, and societal impact.
args.justification: The conceptual entity about ethical dilemmas in AI clearly belongs with other AI ethics concepts under the same Class_Group.

args.new_description: Documents and textual resources focused on ethical dilemmas in AI development and deployment.
args.justification: The document entity about ethical dilemmas in AI should be in a separate, document-focused class but still connected to AI ethics via the shared Class_Group.

args.new_description: This class was split into a conceptual dilemmas class and a document-focused class and currently has no members; retained only for traceability and scheduled for deprecation or merging.
args.remark: This class is now empty after splitting its members; consider removing or fully deprecating it in the next cleanup phase.
args.justification: After splitting the mixed members out, the source class is effectively obsolete; marking it deprecated and aligning Class_Group clarifies its transitional status.
